commit.message: Update Dockerfile to a more recent version
Add CI for Dockerfile
add build matrix
update actions version
use qt5-qmake
use ubuntu 22.04

Revert "Error out if error happens in fast import process"

This reverts commit 58839fa6875ec19fbb7fa70c4b7d538313e759f1.
Notes on end slash requirement
Do not warn the user if default branch does not exist
Error out if error happens in fast import process

Support git default branch name

- Instead of master use the `init.defaultBranch`
  if set.

Fix some typos in the README and add a pointer to where annotated tags
are to be found after the conversion.
Fail test execution if there were duplicate test names (#106)
Add test that copying a directory with empty sub-dirs should put empty .gitignore files to empty directories with empty-dirs parameter

Fix missing .gitignore in empty dirs on dir rename

The commandline option --empty-dirs now also has effect when a directory
is moved in svn.
Do not replace filled gitignore files with empty ones
Add gitignore placeholders for empty directories in branches when using svn-branches and empty-dirs parameter
Remove an empty directory .gitignore placeholder once the directory becomes non-empty
Fix .gitignore handling in root directory
Add nested variations of tests
If svn-ignore should have added a .gitignore file, do not overwrite it with an empty one
Remove .gitignore file if all ignores were removed or the properties deleted
Do not dump added directories multiple times if svn-properties or empty-dirs is used
Add some tests for empty-dirs parameter
Use base fixture from tar to prevent permission problems
Exit with non-zero exit code and usage if not giving exactly one repository
Obey svn-ignore parameter on branching with svn-branches parameter being used
Add Bats tests
